Round 1:
[Patient] Can you recommend safe exercises for someone in my neighborhood?
[Educator] Walking in well-lit areas or doing chair exercises can be good options.

Round 2:
[Patient] Are there any exercises I can do at home without equipment?
[Educator] You can try bodyweight exercises like squats, push-ups, and lunges.

Round 3:
[Patient] How often should I exercise to help my heart failure?
[Educator] Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate exercise most days of the week.

Round 4:
[Patient] Is it safe for me to lift weights with heart failure?
[Educator] Start with light weights and focus on proper form to avoid strain.

Round 5:
[Patient] Can I do yoga or meditation for my heart health?
[Educator] Yes, yoga and meditation can help reduce stress and improve overall well-being.